---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Reading List — Yannik Peschke" 
  description="Books and reading recommendations about software engineering, architecture, and system design."
>

<h1>Reading List</h1>
<p class="page-intro">
  Besides all the work and my hobbies, I love to read. Here are some of my favorite books.
</p>

<h2>AI & Society</h2>
<div class="book-list">
  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Scary Smart: The Future of Artificial Intelligence and How You Can Save Our World</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Mo Gawdat</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        A practical and thought-provoking look at how AI will reshape society, and why human values and incentives
        matter just as much as technical capability.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">AI</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Society</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Ethics</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>The Shallows: How the Internet Is Changing the Way We Think</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Nicholas Carr</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        A sharp exploration of how digital environments shape attention, cognition, and depth of thought—useful
        context for anyone building (or living in) software.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Attention</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Internet</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Thinking</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Focus & Productivity</h2>
<div class="book-list">
  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Deep Work: Rules for Focused Success in a Distracted World</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Cal Newport</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        A framework for producing high-quality work in less time by training focus, reducing distraction, and
        building deliberate routines.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Focus</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Craft</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Habits</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Slow Productivity: The Lost Art of Accomplishment Without Burnout</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Cal Newport</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        A counter-model to frantic “busy work”: fewer projects, more depth, and sustainable output over long
        horizons.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Productivity</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Burnout</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Sustainability</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Getting Things Done: The Art of Stress-free Productivity</h3>
      <p class="book-author">David Allen</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        A classic system for capturing commitments, clarifying next actions, and reducing cognitive load so your
        mind stays clear for creative work.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Systems</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Planning</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Execution</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Minimalism & Intentional Living</h2>
<div class="book-list">
  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Digital Minimalism: Choosing a Focused Life in a Noisy World</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Cal Newport</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        A philosophy and playbook for reclaiming attention by intentionally choosing which technologies deserve
        a place in your life.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Minimalism</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Attention</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Technology</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Essentialism: The Disciplined Pursuit of Less</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Greg McKeown</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        A clear framework for prioritizing what matters most and designing life around the few things that move
        the needle.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Priorities</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Simplicity</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Decision Making</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Craft & Engineering Mindset</h2>
<div class="book-list">
  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>The Pragmatic Programmer: Your Journey to Mastery</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Andrew Hunt, David Thomas</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        Timeless guidance on becoming a better builder: practical habits, clear thinking, and an emphasis on
        responsibility, feedback, and continuous improvement.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Craft</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Pragmatism</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Fundamentals</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Endurance & Running</h2>
<div class="book-list">
  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Born to Run</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Christopher McDougall</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        A story-driven exploration of endurance running, movement, and why humans are built to go long—equal parts
        adventure, culture, and physiology.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Running</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Endurance</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Story</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Eat &amp; Run: My Unlikely Journey to Ultramarathon Greatness</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Scott Jurek</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        Memoir and training perspective from an ultrarunning legend—useful for mindset, consistency, and what it
        takes to keep showing up.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Ultrarunning</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Memoir</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Training</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Finding Ultra</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Rich Roll</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        A transformation story centered on endurance sports and lifestyle changes—great for long-term habit change
        and identity shifts.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Endurance</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Habits</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Transformation</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>The Rise of the Ultra Runners: A Journey to the Edge of Human Endurance</h3>
      <p class="book-author">Adharanand Finn</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        A journalist’s deep dive into the ultrarunning world—culture, training, and the weird beauty of going
        farther than seems sensible.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Ultrarunning</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Culture</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Training</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Resilience & Performance</h2>
<div class="book-list">
  <div class="book-item">
    <div class="book-info">
      <h3>Can&#39;t Hurt Me: Master Your Mind and Defy the Odds</h3>
      <p class="book-author">David Goggins</p>
      <p class="book-description">
        A hard-edged memoir about building resilience through discomfort. Read it for intensity, self-honesty, and
        the psychology of doing difficult things.
      </p>
      <div class="book-tags">
        <span class="book-tag">Mindset</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Resilience</span>
        <span class="book-tag">Discipline</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

</Layout>

<style>
.page-intro {
  font-size: 1.125rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
}

h2 {
  margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
}

h2:first-of-type {
  margin-top: 0;
}

.book-list {
  display: grid;
  gap: var(--spacing-lg);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
}

.book-item {
  padding: var(--spacing-md);
  padding-left: var(--spacing-lg);
  border-left: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  background: transparent;
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
  position: relative;
}

.book-item:hover {
  border-left-color: var(--accent);
  padding-left: calc(var(--spacing-lg) + 10px);
}

.book-item:last-child {
  border-left: 1px solid var(--border-color);
}

.book-item:last-child:hover {
  border-left-color: var(--accent);
}

.book-info h3 {
  font-size: 1.375rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  color: var(--text-primary);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
}

.book-info h3::before {
  content: ">";
  margin-right: 10px;
  color: var(--accent);
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateX(-10px);
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
}

.book-item:hover .book-info h3::before {
  opacity: 1;
  transform: translateX(0);
}

.book-item:hover .book-info h3 {
  color: var(--accent);
}

.book-author {
  font-family: var(--font-main);
  font-size: 14px;
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}

.book-description {
  font-size: 1rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.6;
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
}

.book-tags {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--spacing-xs);
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.book-tag {
  font-family: var(--font-main);
  font-size: 11px;
  padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

</style>
